    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> potatoes </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-8 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>venison & pork patty[ies]</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Sprinkle <strong>half</strong> your <strong>dried thyme </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> on the patty[ies]</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once your potatoes are fork-tender, add your <strong>clotted cream</strong>, the <strong>remaining dried thyme</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the potatoes are well coated \u2013 these are your <strong>thyme clotted cream potatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>thyme clotted cream potatoes</strong> to the baking tray[s] with the patty[ies] and reserve the bowl</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-18 min or until the patty[ies] are cooked through (no pink meat!) and the potatoes are golden and crispy</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, chop your <strong>dried cranberries</strong> roughly</p><p>Wipe the reserved bowl clean and add the <strong>chopped dried cranberries</strong>, cover with <strong>boiled water</strong> and set aside to soften</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s] </strong>in half (if required!)</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are tender and crisp and the patty[ies] cooked through, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Drain the <strong>soaked cranberries</strong>, discarding the soaking liquid</p><p>Top your <strong>venison & pork patty[ies] </strong>with the<strong> soaked cranberries</strong> and <strong>sliced cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>brioche halves </strong>cut side up, to the tray[s], then return to the oven for a final 4-5 min or until warmed through and golden</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-tray-cheesy-venison-and-pork-burger-and-clotted-cream-roast-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To build your burger, divide your <strong>mayo</strong> between each <strong>warmed brioche base</strong>, then<strong> </strong>top each <strong>warmed brioche base </strong>with some <strong>salad </strong>and a <strong>venison & pork patty </strong>and<strong> </strong>then top with a <strong>warmed brioche lid </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> cheesy cranberry venison & pork burger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>thyme clotted cream potatoes</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>salad</strong> to the side, then drizzle the salad with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
